betterquesting:10.name:8: The Numbers Mason, What Do They Mean?!
betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The following is an all inclusive list of valid rack components and their properties. Anything not listed has no effect on computation or heat. If you are struggling with all the numbers and equations, you might want to check the wiki.

[note]Circuit - Computation - Heat Limit - Heat Constant[/note]

Crystalprocessor - 60 - 2000 - 56
Crystalprocessor Assembly - 80 - 2000 - 54
Ultimate Crystalcomputer - 100 - 2000 - 52
Crystalprocessor Mainframe - 120 - 2000 - 50

CPU (Tier 3) - 80 - 2000 - 46
Graphics Card (Tier 3) - 3 - 100 - 2000 - 44
APU (Tier 2) - 120 - 2000 - 42
APU (Tier 3) - 240 - 2000 - 40

Wetware Processor - 160 - 4000 - 46
Wetwareprocessor Assembly - 180 - 4000 - 44
Wetware Supercomputer - 200 - 4000 - 42
Wetware Mainframe - 220 - 4000 - 40

Bioprocessor - 200 - 6000 - 36
Biowareprocessor Assembly - 220 - 6000 - 34
Bioware Supercomputer - 240 - 6000 - 32
Bio Mainframe - 260 - 6000 - 30

Optical Processor - 200 - 8000 - 26
Optical Assembly - 220 - 8000 - 24
Optical Computer - 240 - 8000 - 22
Optical Mainframe - 260 - 8000 - 20

Pico Circuit - 260 - 9500 - 12
Quantum Circuit - 320 - 10000 - 10

[note]Vent - Heat Limit - Cooling Constant[/note]

Heat Vent - 2000 - 40
Reactor Heat Vent - 4000 - 80
Overclocked Heat Vent - 6000 - 120
Advanced Heat Vent - 8000 - 160
Cooling Core - 10000 - 200
